'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2830] on 8 October 2000 at 11:05:01 pm'!"Change Set:		StickyFix-arDate:			8 October 2000Author:			Andreas RaabPrevent world menu when clicking on sticky morphs."!!PasteUpMorph methodsFor: 'event handling' stamp: 'ar 10/8/2000 23:03'!morphToGrab: event	"Return the morph to grab from a mouse down event. If none, return nil."	self submorphsDo:[:m|		(m isLocked not and:[m fullContainsPoint: event cursorPoint]) ifTrue:[^m].	].	^nil! !!PasteUpMorph methodsFor: 'event handling' stamp: 'ar 10/8/2000 23:03'!mouseDown: evt	"Handle a mouse down event."	| grabbedMorph |	grabbedMorph _ self morphToGrab: evt.	grabbedMorph ifNotNil:[		grabbedMorph isSticky ifTrue:[^self].		grabbedMorph isPartsDonor 			ifTrue:[^grabbedMorph partRepresented duplicateMorph: evt].		^evt hand grabMorph: grabbedMorph].	(super handlesMouseDown: evt)		ifTrue:[^super mouseDown: evt].	evt hand halo: nil. "shake off halos"	evt hand releaseKeyboardFocus. "shake of keyboard foci"	evt shiftPressed ifTrue:[^self dragThroughOnDesktop: evt].	self isWorldMorph ifTrue:[self addAlarm: #invokeWorldMenu: with: evt after: 200].! !